= ⬡ QUARTER II GATHERING — The Green Work

*Theme:* Comparative tasting and observation of student macerated tinctures; the inner Nigredo.

#hm-note[
  No two tinctures or salts will be identical, even from the same herb. Discuss
  this with the students — it is its own teaching on the role of the operator
  and the specific timing of each work.
]

*Students bring:*
- Their completed or in-progress Melissa tincture (macerate, poured off).
- Their calcined salt, in whatever stage of color it has reached.
- Their lunar tracking journal from Month 5.
- A brief sharing on what their own calcination process has felt like inwardly.

*Practice:*
The group conducts a comparative tasting of the tinctures (diluted in distilled
water). Color, scent, and taste are discussed.

